        },
        "A_j": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": [
            "tgt_cells"
          ],
          "description": "Target-cell area denominator A_j = \u03a3_i A_ij \u2014 the group-by-`j` row-sum over the bin-Skolem CANDIDATE pairs (join.on [[src_bin,tgt_bin]] on the MATERIALISED bin buffers) with the sub-atol sliver filter. d(A_j[j])/dt from a zero IC \u21d2 du = A_j[j]; the test asserts it reproduces the supplied `dst_areas` (PoU by construction, \u00a75.8.3)."
        },
        "F_tgt": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": [
            "tgt_cells"
          ],
          "description": "Regridded field F_tgt[j] = (1/dst_areas[j])\u00b7\u03a3_i A_ij[i,j]\u00b7F_src[i] = \u03a3_i W_ij\u00b7F_src[i], W_ij = A_ij/A_j \u2014 the apply sum_product FAQ over the bin-Skolem candidate set with the normalize `/ dst_areas[j]` folded in. d(F_tgt[j])/dt from a zero IC \u21d2 du = F_tgt[j]."
        },
        "dst_areas": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [
            "tgt_cells"
          ],
          "description": "Build-once target-cell area denominator A_j = \u03a3_i A_ij stored at regridder-build time (ConservativeRegridding.jl's `dst_areas`). The NORMALIZE factor the apply body divides by; supplied as a const_array. The `A_j` FAQ recomputes the same row-sum to prove the group-by reproduces it (partition-of-unity by construction, \u00a75.8.3)."
        },
        "narrow_phase_area": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Tracer consuming the representative narrow-phase area so the spherical clip + polygon_area FAQ evaluate in a well-formed ODE: d(narrow_phase_area)/dt = A_ij_rep from a zero IC \u21d2 du = A_ij_rep. The conformance test checks it equals polygon_area(clip,\"spherical\") (the kept Van Oosterom-Strackee oracle) and the matching A_ij entry."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "(1a) OVERLAP PAIRS \u2014 bin each SOURCE cell to an integer lat-lon bin key. floor(lon/dx), floor(lat/dy) are integer bin coordinates (the existing `floor` op); skolem mints the content-addressed bin key. Per-element map (output i, no contraction).",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": [
              "src_bin",
              "i"
            ]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": [
              "i"
            ],
            "ranges": {
              "i": {
                "from": "src_cells"
              }
            },
            "args": [
              "src_lon",
              "src_lat",
              "dx",
              "dy"
            ],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "/",
                      "args": [
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": [
                            "src_lon",
                            "i"
                          ]
                        },
                        "dx"
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "/",
                      "args": [
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": [
                            "src_lat",
                            "i"
                          ]
                        },
                        "dy"
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(1b) OVERLAP PAIRS \u2014 bin each TARGET cell identically (same dx/dy quantization).",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": [
              "tgt_bin",
              "j"
            ]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": [
              "j"
            ],
            "ranges": {
              "j": {
                "from": "tgt_cells"
              }
            },
            "args": [
              "tgt_lon",
              "tgt_lat",
              "dx",
              "dy"
            ],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "/",
                      "args": [
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": [
                            "tgt_lon",
                            "j"
                          ]
                        },
                        "dx"
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "op": "floor",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "/",
                      "args": [
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": [
                            "tgt_lat",
                            "j"
                          ]
                        },
                        "dy"
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(1c) OVERLAP PAIRS \u2014 the candidate overlap-pair set = the bin-Skolem EQUI-join. The index-set-producing aggregate (bool_and_or, distinct:true, id `candidate_set` referenced by candidate_pairs.from_faq) ranges source i and target j, the M2 `join.on` keeps only (i,j) whose bin keys are EQUAL, and skolem(\"pair\", i, j) names each surviving candidate; the `true` body marks membership. Integer bin keys \u21d2 the candidate set is byte-identical across bindings in the \u00a75.7 sorted order (\u00a75.8.5). No spatial-index op in the IR \u2014 the index is a physical-operator concern (STR-tree acceleration is the perf follow-on, out of scope).",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "index",
            "args": [
              "pair_exists",
              "p"
            ]
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "id": "candidate_set",
            "semiring": "bool_and_or",
            "distinct": true,
            "output_idx": [
              "p"
            ],
            "ranges": {
              "i": {
                "from": "src_cells"
              },
              "j": {
                "from": "tgt_cells"
              }
            },
            "join": [
              {
                "on": [
                  [
                    "src_bin",
                    "tgt_bin"
                  ]
                ]
              }
            ],
            "args": [
              "src_bin",
              "tgt_bin"
            ],
            "key": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "pair",
                "i",
                "j"
              ]
            },
            "expr": {
              "op": "true",
              "args": []
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "NARROW-PHASE DEMO consumer: d(narrow_phase_area)/dt = A_ij_rep, the representative spherical polygon_area(intersect_polygon(...)) overlap area. A_ij_rep is a scalar observed substituted inline; from a zero IC du = A_ij_rep.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "D",
            "args": [
              "narrow_phase_area"
            ],
            "wrt": "t"
          },
          "rhs": "A_ij_rep"
        },
        {
          "_comment": "(3) A_j[j] = \u03a3_i A_ij[i,j] \u2014 the group-by-`j` sum_product FAQ. The OVERLAP JOIN restricts the contraction to bin-Skolem CANDIDATE pairs by gating on the MATERIALISED bin buffers: join.on [[src_bin,tgt_bin]] admits (i,j) iff src_bin[i] == tgt_bin[j] (the F3 buffer-gated join, \u00a75.3). filter A_ij>atol drops sub-atol slivers \u2192 the SURVIVING set. Zero IC \u21d2 du[A_j[j]] = A_j[j].",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": [
              "j"
            ],
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [
                {
                  "op": "index",
                  "args": [
                    "A_j",
                    "j"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "wrt": "t"
            },
            "ranges": {
              "j": [
                1,
                3
              ]
            }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "output_idx": [
              "j"
            ],
            "ranges": {
              "i": {
                "from": "src_cells"
              },
              "j": {
                "from": "tgt_cells"
              }
            },
